The deposed Emir of Kano, Muhammadu Sanusi II, on Friday afternoon, left Awe, Nasarawa State, where he was earlier banished to by the Kano State Government. Our correspondent, who was in Awe, reported that Sanusi left the town in company with the Kaduna State Governor, Nasir El-Rufai, who had come on a visit to him. Earlier, a Federal High Court in Abuja ordered the police and Department of State Service to release Sanusi from confinement. Governor El-Rufai confirmed that they are heading to Abuja. The Kaduna governor also uploaded a picture showing the former Emir and himself in a vehicle. Details laterâ€¦ 